'''Ōtsu Shrine''' (大津神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in {{ill|Kamioka|ja|神岡町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamioka|qq=}}, [[Hida City]], [[Gifu Prefecture]]. It is designated as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}, a prefectural shrine, and a special {{ill|Kinpei-sha|ja|金幣社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinpei-sha|qq=}}.

== Enshrined Deities ==
; Main Shrine
* {{ill|Prince Ōhiko|ja|大彦命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Ōhiko|qq=}}
* {{ill|Takenu Nakawawake no Mikoto|ja|武渟河別命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takenu Nakawawake no Mikoto|qq=}} - Son of Ōhiko no Mikoto.
* {{ill|Takeminakata|lt=Takeminakata no Mikoto|ja|建南方富命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata|qq=}} - Enshrined from {{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Shrine|qq=}}.

; Auxiliary Shrines
* Shinmei Shrine
''' {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu Ōmikami|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu|qq=}}
* Mizunami Shrine
''' {{ill|Mizuhanome|lt=Mizuhanome no Kami|ja|水波能売大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizuhanome|qq=}}
* Akiba Shrine
''' {{ill|Hi no Kagutsuchi|ja|火彦霊大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hi no Kagutsuchi|qq=}}
* Ōyama-tsumi Shrine
''' {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ltt=Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=}}
* Suminawa Shrine
''' {{ill|Hikosashiri no Kami|ja|彦狭知大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikosashiri no Kami|qq=}}
''' {{ill|Teojihori no Kami|ja|手置帆負大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Teojihori no Kami|qq=}}
''' Spirit of the Hida Master Craftsman
* Tsushima Shrine
''' {{ill|Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|建速須佐之男大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}}
* Kōzan Shrine
''' {{ill|Kanayamahiko no Kami|ja|金山彦大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanayamahiko no Kami|qq=}}
''' {{ill|Kanayamahime no Kami|ja|金山姫大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanayamahime no Kami|qq=}}
* Sugawara Shrine
''' {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=}}
''' {{ill|Kotoshironushi|lt=Kotoshironushi no Kami|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=}}
''' {{ill|Ebisu|ja|恵美須大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebisu|qq=}}
* Sarutahiko Shrine
''' {{ill|Sarutahiko Ōkami|ja|猿田彦大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sarutahiko Ōkami|qq=}}

; Subordinate Shrines
* Inari Shrine
''' {{ill|Uka no Mitama no Kami|ja|宇賀御霊大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uka no Mitama no Kami|qq=}}
* Kodama Shrine
''' {{ill|Kukunochi no Kami|ja|久久能智大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kukunochi no Kami|qq=}}

== History ==
The exact origins of the shrine are unknown. Records from the {{ill|Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku|ja|日本文徳天皇実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku|qq=}} and the {{ill|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|ja|日本三代実録|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|qq=}} suggest that rituals were being conducted at the shrine during the early [[Heian period]]. It is listed among the eight shrines of [[Hida Province]] in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}}.

During the {{ill|Kenmu|ja|建武|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenmu|qq=}} era, the local lord {{ill|Ema Clan|ja|江馬氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ema Clan|qq=}} invited a divided spirit of the {{ill|Suwa Daimyōjin|ja|諏訪大明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Daimyōjin|qq=}}, changing the shrine's name to Suwa Daimyōjin. Following periods of rule by the Ema, {{ill|Miki Clan|ja|三木氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miki Clan|qq=}}, and {{ill|Kanamori Clan|ja|金森氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanamori Clan|qq=}}, the shrine's original name was restored in 1804 after extensive research by followers of {{ill|Tanaka Ōhide|ja|田中大秀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanaka Ōhide|qq=}}.

In 1871, under the {{ill|Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|1=Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|13=User:Immanuelle/Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=}}, Ōtsu Shrine was designated a prefectural shrine. In 1930, it was elevated to special {{ill|Kinpei-sha|ja|金幣社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinpei-sha|qq=}} status.

== Grounds ==
* Main Shrine
* Auxiliary Shrines
* Handwashing Basin
* First Torii Gate (completed in 1928)
* Second Torii Gate

