{{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | name=Ōtsu Shrine | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image=[[File:Otsu-jinja Kamioka ac (2).jpg|280px]] | location=[[Gifu Prefecture]], [[Hida City]], {{ill|Kamioka|ja|神岡町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamioka|qq=}}, Ōaza Funatsu | coordinates={{Coord|36|20|4.4|N|137|17|39.4|E}} | deity={{ill|Prince Ōhiko|ja|大彦命|1=Ōhiko-no-Mikoto|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Ōhiko|qq=}}, {{ill|Takenu Nakawawake no Mikoto|ja|武渟河別命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takenu Nakawawake no Mikoto|qq=}}, {{ill|Takeminakata no Mikoto|ja|建南方富命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata no Mikoto|qq=}} | type={{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}, Prefectural Shrine, Special {{ill|Kinpei-sha|ja|金幣社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinpei-sha|qq=}} | consecration_year=Unknown | festival=4th Saturday of April }}
'''Ōtsu Shrine''' (大津神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in {{ill|Kamioka|ja|神岡町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamioka|qq=}}, [[Hida City]], [[Gifu Prefecture]]. It is designated as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}, a prefectural shrine, and a special {{ill|Kinpei-sha|ja|金幣社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinpei-sha|qq=}}.
== Enshrined Deities == ; Main Shrine * {{ill|Prince Ōhiko|ja|大彦命|1=Ōhiko-no-Mikoto|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prince Ōhiko|qq=}} * {{ill|Takenu Nakawawake no Mikoto|ja|武渟河別命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takenu Nakawawake no Mikoto|qq=}} - Son of Ōhiko-no-Mikoto. * {{ill|Takeminakata|lt=Takeminakata no Mikoto|ja|建南方富命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata|qq=}} - Enshrined from {{ill|Suwa Shrine|ja|諏訪神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Shrine|qq=}}.
; Auxiliary Shrines * Shinmei Shrine ''' [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]] * Mizunami Shrine ''' {{ill|Mizuhanome|lt=Mizuhanome no Kami|ja|水波能売大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mizuhanome|qq=}} * Akiba Shrine ''' {{ill|Hi no Kagutsuchi|ja|火彦霊大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hi no Kagutsuchi|qq=}} * Ōyama-tsumi Shrine ''' {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ltt=Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi|qq=}} * Suminawa Shrine ''' {{ill|Hikosashiri no Kami|ja|彦狭知大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikosashiri no Kami|qq=}} ''' {{ill|Teojihori no Kami|ja|手置帆負大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Teojihori no Kami|qq=}} ''' Spirit of the Hida Master Craftsman * Tsushima Shrine ''' {{ill|Susanoo|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|建速須佐之男大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo|13=User:Immanuelle/Susanoo-no-Mikoto|qq=}} * Kōzan Shrine ''' {{ill|Kanayamahiko no Kami|ja|金山彦大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanayamahiko no Kami|qq=}} ''' {{ill|Kanayamahime no Kami|ja|金山姫大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanayamahime no Kami|qq=}} * Sugawara Shrine ''' {{ill|Sugawara no Michizane|ja|Sugawara no Michizane|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sugawara no Michizane|qq=}} ''' {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi|lt=Kotoshironushi no Kami|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=}} ''' {{ill|Ebisu|ja|恵美須大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ebisu|qq=}} * Sarutahiko Shrine ''' {{ill|Sarutahiko Ōkami|ja|猿田彦大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sarutahiko Ōkami|qq=}}
; Subordinate Shrines * Inari Shrine ''' {{ill|Uka no Mitama no Kami|ja|宇賀御霊大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Uka no Mitama no Kami|qq=}} * Kodama Shrine ''' {{ill|Kukunochi no Kami|ja|久久能智大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kukunochi no Kami|qq=}}
== History == The exact origins of the shrine are unknown. Records from the [[:en:Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku|Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku]] and the [[:en:Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]] suggest that rituals were being conducted at the shrine during the early [[Heian period]]. It is listed among the eight shrines of [[Hida Province]] in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}}.
During the [[:en:Jianwu|Kenmu]] era, the local lord {{ill|Ema Clan|ja|江馬氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ema Clan|qq=}} invited a divided spirit of the {{ill|Suwa Daimyōjin|ja|諏訪大明神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Daimyōjin|qq=}}, changing the shrine's name to Suwa Daimyōjin. Following periods of rule by the Ema, {{ill|Miki Clan|ja|三木氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miki Clan|qq=}}, and {{ill|Kanamori Clan|ja|金森氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanamori Clan|qq=}}, the shrine's original name was restored in 1804 after extensive research by followers of [[:en:Tanaka Ōhide|Tanaka Ōhide]].
In 1871, under the [[:en:Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines]], Ōtsu Shrine was designated a prefectural shrine. In 1930, it was elevated to special {{ill|Kinpei-sha|ja|金幣社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinpei-sha|qq=}} status.
== Grounds == * Main Shrine * Auxiliary Shrines * Handwashing Basin * First Torii Gate (completed in 1928) * Second Torii Gate
<gallery> Otsu-jinja Kamioka ac (3).jpg|Auxiliary Shrines Otsu-jinja Kamioka ac (5).jpg|Administrative Office Otsu-jinja Kamioka ac (4).jpg|Handwashing Basin Otsu-jinja Kamioka ac (6).jpg|First Torii Gate </gallery>
== Festivals == === Kamioka Festival === The collective term for the annual festivals of Ōtsu Shrine, [[:en:Hachiman shrine|Hachiman Shrine (Hida City)]], and {{ill|Hakusan Shrine (Hida City)|ja|白山神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hakusan Shrine (Hida City)|qq=}}, celebrated on the same day. It is one of the "Three Great Festivals of Hida," alongside the [[:en:Takayama Festival|Takayama Festival]] and {{ill|Furukawa Festival|ja|古川祭|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furukawa Festival|qq=}}.
=== Funatsu Bon Odori === Held annually from August 14 to 16 in the shrine precincts. It was designated as an intangible cultural property by [[Gifu Prefecture]] in 1969.<ref>{{Cite web|language=ja|date= |url=http://www.pref.gifu.lg.jp/kyoiku-bunka-sports/bunka-geijutsu/bunkazai-zuroku/bunkazai-zuroku/mumin/hidasi/funatubonn.html |title=Funatsu Bon Odori |publisher=Gifu Prefecture |accessdate=2012-10-16}}</ref>
